post_text: Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures.The P-EBT application will open the first week of June. P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Brownwood Education Foundation
March 25 at 7:33 PM ¬∑

A Note From Superintendent Joe Young
üåê‚¨áÔ∏èüì¢
Transitioning to off-campus instruction is difficult. In a time when our world is turning upside down, you don‚Äôt need more pressure without support. Parents: do your best. Period. Nothing more is expected or possible. You still have full-time responsibilities that existed before you became an educator as well. Don‚Äôt let the work we are providing become a burden. The material is to help you guide your students through a new chapter. If you struggle, reach out to us; that‚Äôs normal. We struggle‚Ä¶ and it‚Äôs our full-time job. If you have a success, share it; we want to celebrate with you. You love your kids and want them to succeed, and so do we. Using the resources at https://www.brownwoodisd.org/oci, we will make this work together. If you only remind your students each day that you love them and that education is important, your day is a success. Communicate how we can help make this process better. #BwdPride #lionpride #brownwoodtough #doyourbest #shareyoursuccess

We do ask that you do not alter or crop the logo at the bottom of the picture because it helps model copyright for the students!

If you would like to purchase a print of your favorite student, please visit https://bhsmediacrew.smugmug.com/Brownwood-High-School/19-20-Youth-Fair All proceeds from these prints goes to the BHS Media Crew and we would LOVE your support!

Carl Wayne is with Stacee Hetzel and Heather Hohertz-Perez.
December 28, 2019 at 11:41 PM ¬∑

Great showing by the Brownwood teams in the Texas bank holiday classic basketball tournament. In fact congratulations to the Brownwood Lady Lions capturing the girls championship for the second straight year; and the Brownwood JV boys capturing the small school boys championship with five victories over varsity teams. And the Brownwood lions boys varsity finished strong as well going 3-1.. overall a great tournament!
